<br>
I crossed the room to the basin of water in the corner, splashing my face with it and preparing for the day.  I pulled my armor from the stand and dressed myself.  Sitting on the bed, donning my boots, I began to think.   I had only one guess where I could find my husband.  Shaking my head of the thoughts of having to retrieve him from that incipid mold factory he'd become a fiend for. <br>
<br>
I peeked out my door, hoping to see him strolling down the hall.  'No luck', I thought.  Just as I was about to close the door, I kicked a scroll that had been slid under the door.  I unrolled the parchment and began to read:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Restoria,<br>
I am in need of a priest and warrior to aid me in the settling of an old score with the Mistress Drusilla of Sathir.  If you would accompany me, I assure you it will be nothing short of an adventure.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
I stopped reading for a moment, 'With the way you pull, there's no doubt.'  I chuckled to myself.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   If you would be so good as to join me, contact Baron Witherweaver Wyntari and he will provide the transportation  to lessen your travel time.<br>
<br>
                                                  Regards,<br>
                                                  Qixx </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Being on the moon has its disadvantages, for I could not gage the time of day and hadn't a clue how long the scroll lay underneath my door.  I gathered my bags and set out to find Kritical.  I strolled onto the cobblestone streets of Shadow Haven, which showed a decent amount of activity from the shoppers and tavern patrons in the streets.  &quot;Hmm must still be early yet... good.&quot;<br>
<br>
I continued through the Caverns and into the dank dark swamplands of the Grove.  Just as I suspected, there he was, doused in fungal fluids from harvesting the shrieker mushrooms.  Quite a delicasy in soup, I might add.<br>
<br>
&quot;Up for some adventure, my love?&quot;<br>
<br>
He hacked into the last remaining mushroom and looked up at me, wiping the sweat from his brow.<br>
<br>
&quot;I suppose I could be persueded.&quot; He grinned.<br>
<br>
I smiled mischieviously,&quot;It will provide quite an experience.. Qixx invited us.&quot;<br>
<br>
He chuckled.  &quot;Sure, lets go.&quot;<br>
<br>
I sent word upon the winds for Witherweaver to meet us in the marketplace known as the Bazarre, hoping that would allow us time to stop by the inn and get the smell of fungus off Krit's armor.<br>
<br>
&quot;Walk down wind please.&quot; I grinned, holding my nose and quickening my pace to avoid the musky smell.<br>
<br>
'Haha! Suffer!&quot; He shouted, running after me and grabbing me around the waste, hugging me tightly.<br>
<br>
I sighed, resolved to live with the stench.  &quot;Well, we've smelled worse I suppose.&quot; I giggled.<br>
<br>
When we reached the Bazarre, Witherweaver was waiting for us.  The Tier 'Dal stood proud in his dark green robe, threaded with royal blue insignias.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ready you two?&quot; He spoke human tongue as well as I, and he motioned for us to join and we went to a quiet area near the stables so he could chant the portal spell with no interruptions.<br>
<br>
His incantation was brief, we disappeared from the marketplace, in a large ball of flame leaving only a little smoke from where we once stood.<br>
<br>
A hole opened up in the sky in the dragon infested lava pits known as Skyfire.  Realizing that we weren't in the most ideal of places, we hurried quickly through, carefully avoiding the wandering wurms.<br>
<br>
Qixx was waiting for us just through the cave separating skyfire from Overthere. &quot;Thanks for coming, guys.&quot; He smiled, grinning his goofy scaled grin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Are we it?&quot; I asked cautiously.<br>
<br>
Qixx chuckled, knowing that walking into our destination would be quite difficult without the aid of a rogue.  &quot;Lolo and Mezz are meeting us at the canyon.&quot;<br>
<br>
'Ahh, a nice test of skill for Mezz' I thought to myself, as he had hopes of wearing the insignia of our guild and I had yet to see his skill for myself to judge.  Sure enough, there stood another Tier'Dal in a shining purple robe, some even thought it to be weaved out of metallic threads.  I didnt see the rogue though.<br>
<br>
Just as that thought passed through my head, a human female clad in black armor emerged from the shadows, the epic ragebringer piercer aimed at the weakest point in Kritical's armor.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gimme all your loots!&quot; she exclaimed, giggling as she poked him with the very tip of the blade.<br>
<br>
Kritical jumped, nearly losing his balance at the edge of the canyon.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Lolo.&quot; Kritical said, turning to her and regaining his composure.<br>
<br>
&quot;I got you so bad!&quot; Lolodory laughed.<br>
<br>
Kritical raised an eyebrow at her, &quot;Bah, I'll deal with you later!&quot; <br>
<br>
Witherweaver dug through his bags and produced a handful of batwings.  He waved his hands quickly, chanting and threw the wings into the air.  They crumbled into dust, and as it rained down upon us, each of us began to float.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thanks Wither.&quot; I said as we started down the large canyon, and through the temple entrance, passing enormous scorpions.  We came to a dead end in the maze,  a red glowing orb in the center.<br>
<br>
&quot;We all have keys, right?&quot; Kritical asked, eager to get on with the adventure.<br>
<br>
Lolodory frowned as she looked through her bags.  &quot;I guess I dont.&quot; she sighed, pulling out a lockpick and attempted to pick the virtually invisible lock holding the orbs door to Charsis from opening.<br>
<br>
&quot;No problem, I'll get MY druid slave to give you one.&quot;  Qixx laughed, calling out his for long time friend Beornn.<br>
<br>
Beornn agreed to bring the rogue a key, and Lolodory suggested we go inside lest we wake the scorpions sleeping nearby.  We stepped into the dungeon also known as Howling Stones, and I began casting protection spells on all of us.  <br>
<br>
'At least I'll have time for some meditation before we start.' I thought to myself, knowing the impatience of my husband to run into battle with me unprepared.<br>
<br>
Lolodory thanked Beornn and stepped inside.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good.  Now we can begin.&quot; Kritical said enthusiastically.<br>
<br>
We carefully explored the underground castle, Qixx running ahead to survey the scene.<br>
<br>
&quot;Through here.&quot; he pointed at a small set of stairs leading to a painting of what appeared to be lizard royalty.  Sure enough, the painting was an illusion, and we walked through it, stumbling a few paces where stairs should have been on the other side.<br>
<br>
The room was filled with a few animated iksar bones and some large stoney golems, who didnt really care for our intrusion.<br>
<br>
Hacking and slashing, kicking, piercing and blasting ensued, and the room was cleared, leaving only dust, and bloodstained walls as a reminder of the guardians of the room.<br>
<br>
We pressed on, deeper through the castle, and came to a hallway where the tapestries looked finer, the candles burned brighter and even the walls looked as though they were comprised of better building material.<br>
<br>
&quot;We must be close.&quot;  Mezzmorizer said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, her room is around the corner.&quot; Qixx whispered. <br>
<br>
&quot;Well, are we ready?&quot;  Kritical asked, looking at me.<br>
<br>
&quot;One moment.&quot;  I answered, kneeling in prayer.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Karana, grant me your wisdom and blessings to protect my friends in this battle. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
With that I arose, instantly feeling better.  Casting final blessings on my friends, we prepared for battle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now Im ready.&quot; I stated calmly.<br>
<br>
That was all the monk needed to hear.  He disappeared around the corner.<br>
<br>
&quot;Qixx pull incomming!&quot; he shouted, running back to us and falling to the ground, allowing Kritical to taunt  the foes.<br>
<br>
Mezzmorizer chanted quickly, and the additional mobs grew silent, standing as if statues, forgetting why they had been angered in the first place, allowing Kritical to focus on the royal mistress of the castle herself, Drusilla of Sathir.<br>
<br>
Kritical swung fiercly, slahing at the lizard boned mistress with dual swords whirring through the air, making a voilent 'clang!'  as it sheered through her bones.<br>
<br>
Lolodory ran behind, avoiding the large boney tail, swinging menacingly and piercing the weakened remaining flesh of the her back, and poking into the spine.<br>
<br>
Flames danced on Witherweaver's fingers as he chanted loudly, eyes closed in concentration.  Loud booms erupted in the air and the smell of singed bones followed each incantation.<br>
<br>
Qixx jumped up into the air, landing clawed feet at her skull with precision.<br>
<br>
I watched, a few steps away, for any sign of weakness or injury from my party members, ready to cure them and send them back into battle as new.  I shouted out the ancient words, pouring a celestial elixir onto my husband, watching his health renew over the course of the battle.<br>
<br>
One of Drusilla's guardian golems awoke from his magical dreamworld, recalling who had made him drousy, he ran straight at Mezzmorizer.  Knowing illusionists have little stamina for combat battle, I thought quickly, and chanted one of my oldest spells, taught to me in the earliest days of clericing.  <br>
<br>
The golem froze, shaking its head violently.. stunned.  This allowed Mezz the time to recant his spell, putting the beast back into his magic enduced slumber.<br>
<br>
The battle raged on, all 6 of us testing the limits of our abilities in the close quarters of this hallway.<br>
<br>
Soon after, all the foes lay still at the feet of my party, a gory pile of bloody flesh, crumpled bones and stone.<br>
<br>
We collapsed to the ground, resting a moment from the furious battle.<br>
<br>
&quot;So Qixx, what was this old score we just settled with her?&quot; I asked, helping everyone dress their wounds.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing really,&quot; he grinned. &quot;I just wanted to piss Venril off.&quot;<br>
<br>
We all laughed as he knelt over the marrow that once was Drusilla.  &quot;But we got this.&quot;  He smiled.. scooping up a vial of tears.<br>
<br>
We all grinned, the thrill of the battle would have to suffice this time.... perhaps the item he seeks is still down that canyon in the underground castle waiting to be found.<br>
<br>
Witherweaver took a handful of shards, circling them around our heads we all disbursed, tired and hungry to retreat to our camps and prepare to explore another day.<br>
