<br>
My head flew up off a pile of books when a small scroll mysteriously landed upon my desk.  I must have fallen asleep studying again.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Witherweaver.  We require your assistance in the magical art of transportation to venture into the depths of Charasis and kill the vile Drusella Sathir&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Damn it all!&quot; I cursed.  &quot;What am I their damned transportation service?  Don't the recognize my power and my potential?&quot;<br>
<br>
I decided that I should turn on my new gnomish tinkering device contrapted by Bend, our local rogue and tinkerer.  The device crushed beans from a local plant growing in the plains of Karana (a dreaded place indeed), and mixed them in heated water.  It turns out that the beans have a substance in them which makes people more amiable.<br>
<br>
After drinking a long goblet of the dark liquid, I read the letter again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow that feels much better.  I guess I can come.  I never really liked the Sathirs' much, anyway.  Perhaps I can even hone my skills and furhter my study of wizardry.&quot;<br>
<br>
I immediately sent word to Restoria, and her arrogant husband, Kritical: &quot;Get ready I'm coming&quot;.  <br>
<br>
I mumbled some magical incantations and the world around me blurs as I find myself in the wonderous spires of the Nexus.  I made my way to the bazaar to meet the pale-skinned duo.  <br>
<br>
There they were.  All shiny with armor and swords and such.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's go,&quot; I said<br>
<br>
I began to again to mumble some magical incantations, with the intention of bringing us to the volcanic mountaints of Skyfire.  But then a suddent thought struck me.  Perhaps I have been associating myself with these pale skins too long, but I got a feeling of concern for their safety.  I decided I should use my magics to first hide them from view so that wurms and drakes of Skyfire did not eat them alive.  They probably wouldn't last too long there, anyway, without powerful magics such as mine to keep them alive.<br>
<br>
After taking precautionary measures, I mumbled the incantations to bring us to Skyfire.  As the world blurred and cleared up again, I saw Restoria rumbling through her backpacks.<br>
<br>
&quot;For the love of Karana!&quot;  Restoria exclaims, and immediately casts a spell which I recognize as gate.<br>
<br>
I cast a sidewise glance at Kritical.<br>
<br>
&quot;She had forgotten her key in the bazaar,&quot; Kritical explains.<br>
<br>
Witherweaver sighs, clearly dissapointed.  &quot;I suppose I better go meet her then and bring her back.  You go ahead, I'll catch up with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But I don't know the way,&quot; said Kritical.<br>
<br>
Witherweaver sighs, clearly disappointed.  Do they not make maps where pale skins come form?  &quot;I shall be right back.&quot;<br>
<br>
So after another short drip to the Bazaar, we finally begin to make our way to The Overthere, in which lies the ancient estate of Venril Sathir, Charasis, known to adventurers today as Howling Stones, dubbed so no doubt due to the screams of dying adventurers in the depths of the dungeon that can mysteriously be heard above the rocks in the Overthere.<br>
<br>
So we made our way through Skyfire Mountains, dodging the occasional wurm and lava pool.  As we were making our way into the Overthere I found the iksar martial arts master, Qixx.  &quot;Good,&quot; I thought, &quot;we're going to need his experience for this one.&quot;  I rummaged through my packs and found some batwings, and uttered the words to make my friends fly through the air.  &quot;You're going to need this unless you like falling to your death&quot; I explained to them.<br>
<br>
As we were heading towards Charasis, Qixx informed us that Mezzmorizer and Lolodory were still at the undead outpost up north.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Damn it all!   Is this thing ever going to get started?&quot; I thought impatiently.  &quot;I'll get them,&quot; I told my friends.<br>
<br>
I quickly ran up to the outpost at which I had spent many of my earlier years gaining experience in the arts of wizardry.  The gargoyles Corundium and Tourmaline quickly noticed me and smiled my way.  I nodded back at them in recognition, remembered how they used to help me when I was overwhelmed with sarnarks and tigers fighting in the wilderness surrounding the outpost.  It was too bad, they were soon going to think me their enemy because I was about to defy their master.  Oh, well, they are simpletons, and I cannot waste time thinking about simpletons, even those from whom I have benefited in the past.  If they wish to hate me after my experiences, so be it; they won't be the first.<br>
<br>
I found Mezzmorizer dressed in his metallic purple roses, and Lolodory made herself evident soonafter.  &quot;Make sure you cannot be seen&quot; I told them.  &quot;There are dangerous folk on the way.&quot;  I also gave them the gift of flight, as them falling to their deaths would really slow us down.<br>
<br>
Finally we made our way to the massive fissure seeming to tear into the plains of The Overthere.  I brought out a map I had stuffed into my packs before I left my tower.  &quot;According to this map,&quot; I told my friends, &quot;the cave we are looking for is right down there.&quot;  I then jumped off the cliff into the scorpion filled pits below. <br>
<br>
&quot;Follow me and make sure you're flying, not falling.  It's quite a way down,&quot; I told them.<br>
<br>
As we reached the ground Qixx informed us &quot;This passageway here leads us to the entrance of the infamous Howling Stones.  The journey will be difficult but the rewards will be great.  Be on your guard, and be wary of the scorpion creatures around us.  If they spot you they will tear you up in a matter of seconds.&quot;<br>
<br>
We made our way in.<br>
<br>
After crawling through twists and turns around the menacing Scorpikis', I spotted a large red orb.<br>
<br>
&quot;That is the entrance,&quot; Qixx said.  &quot;If you take out your key and turn the lock, you will find yourself magically brought into the dungeon.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's go,&quot; I said, taking out my key.  I quickly found the lock and turned it, and indeed the world around me began to haze as I heard mumbles behind me having something to do with Lolodory.<br>
<br>
When I entered I was on a floating rectangular platform with four paths leading to stairs, at the top of each of which was a golem-guarded door.  Suddenly a skeleton noticed me and drew upon its dark energies.  The skin in my body cringed with pain.  My magical protections has blocked the hardest of it, but I could still feel the energy of pure hatred and evil within this being attempting to destroy my life force.  Then it lunged at me.<br>
<br>
&quot;Damn it where are you guys!  I am under attack!&quot; I screamed into the room, but no one seemed to here.  Have my companions left me to die?  Are they simply too stupid to figure out how to use the lock?  These thoughts went through my mind however useless they were at the time.  But I needed to do something, to immobalize or destroy the skeleton.  But alas I was not concentrating, and even though I managed to immobalize the skeleton he had gashed my chest and torn my robes, and I was bleeding badly.  As I backed away from him sharp teeth dug into my shoulder and I howled out in pain.  The skeleton broke free from my magical binds and crushed my leg.  There was no chance, I had been defeated.<br>
<br>
Darkness evenloped my world, and I regained consciousness in Sanctus Seru where I had bound my spirit.  I convinced myself that my friends would avenge my death and Restoria would bring life back into my spirit.  <br>
<br>
It turns out that my companion's hesitation was due to Lolodory's lack of a key.  The others watched as she unsuccessfully attempted to pick the lock.  But the others found their way in and Restoria renergized my body.  After some preparatory measurements, we proceeded to make our way through the dungeon.  <br>
<br>
The minions of Sathir proved no match to our forces.  We clawed our way through skeletons and golemn and weird amorophous ooze creatures until we finally found Drusella's room.<br>
<br>
When we reached Drusella's room Qixx initiated the combat (I believe I overheard &quot;Hey, bish!  I hear your loved has the hots for Beornn!&quot; - I always wondered what Qixx used to pull.  No wonder how he gets so many mobs pissed at him at once).  Immediately four golems charged our small party, along with a swirling pile of bones that from my lore I identified as the late Drusella Sathir.  Apparently she too has cheated death like her lover, though perhaps undeath isn't quite a cheat.<br>
<br>
Mezzmorizer stopped the golems in their tracks with his magical flashes of light and enchanting images.  I concentrated on destroying whatever it was that remained of Drusella.  Kritical withstood her blows well, while Restoria repaired any damage.  Qixx must have been doing something becaues I cought a glimpse of scaly arms and feet flying through the air.  I wrought forth the raw power of magic upon Drusella, and she fell to our might.  <br>
<br>
We took from Drusella what was on our corpse and I used my powers of transportation to take us back to the floating platform.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; I said, &quot;We have proven our self greater than an ancient pile of bones&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You're always so negative&quot; Kritical responded.  &quot;Now take me back to the Bazaar&quot;<br>
<br>
Witherweaver sighs, clearly disappointed.<br>
<br>
Witherweaver<br>
60 Wizard (I Was 59 when I started writing this)<br>
Fire and Fury<br>
