<br>
In my studies i have found none of my ancient forefathers so amusing and repulsing as this Venril Sathir. For years he has grown powerful and bloated raising his foul necromancy in the heard of the Werewolf city, and living with the dead. Alone i stand no match against this awesome force, but in my travels i have aquired the..... aid... of powerful warriors and mighty weilders of magics. With these forces i would be able to strike into the heart of my beloved land, and clean what filth had grown in the iksar race's reclusion.<br>
<br>
Cloaked in peddlers clothes i traveled the lands of the humans, at each of my companions dwellings tacking a simple note to the door<br>
<br>
&quot;I am in need of help in the settling of an old score with the Mistress Drusella of Sathir. If you would accompany me, I assure you it will be nothing short of an adventure. <br>
<br>
If you would be so good as to join me, contact Baron Witherweaver Wyntari and he will provide the transportation to lessen your travel time.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Qixx &quot;<br>
<br>
At Witherweavers door i tacked a simpler note...<br>
<br>
&quot;Powerful magics to be had, heed your friends calls, come, fight.<br>
-Qixx&quot;<br>
<br>
And come they did. Those that are called Witherweaver, Lolodory, Mezzmorizer, Restoria and Kritical came, powerful beings in their own right, a massive force combined.<br>
<br>
We journeyed to the lands of my ancestors, and deep in the caves overrun with scorpikis, entered the tomb of the once beautiful, sensuous, deadly, Lady Drusella, wife of my enemy.<br>
<br>
Upon entry the choke of dead flesh, and vile good assailed my keen iksar nostrils. With a silent curse to my god, for creating fear in the hearts of mortals, and bestowing me with a slight twinge of his everlasting gift to the world right then, i flung 2 shruiken at the guardians of the entryway. I have no taste for defensive action, and as the horrible skeletal creatures stepped towards me, intent on ripping my heart out, a shining figure stepped in front of me, clad in gleaming silver platemail. My warlord companion's silver blades danced in the dark room like lightning, the blows rebounding off his sturdy armour as his mate, Restoria wove beautiful protective magics around him. With a fiery blast from Witherweaver and a quick thrust from Lolodory, the foul beings were sent back to the eternal rest from which they had been unfairly summoned from.<br>
<br>
Our devious rogue Lolodory claimed she knew no way to open doors, as she had not become proficient in the use of her lockpicks, untill i mentioned the hoard of gold usually stored in the royal iksar crypts. She became unnervingly attentive, and extremely deft with her lockpicks and thenceforth opened any door she deemed might have loot behind it. Many skeletons we laid to rest, many golems turned into dust as i clawed and kicked my way to the royal chambers.<br>
<br>
Finally we came upon it. The ladys door. The woman that loved me and i her, in times long past, that had ventured into the desperate passion of venril, the wife of the man who banished me from her thoughts and her from mine with foul necromancy. In the heat of the moment i remember not what i said, but i am sure it was something to the effect of &quot;Drusella, you are my bish whether you like it or not&quot;, knowing full well how much the female breed of iksar likes to be called &quot;bish&quot;. Roaring out of her room like hell unleashed she came, tearing the walls of her beautiful crypt apart with her fury. (hell hath no fury like a dead woman reborn) <br>
<br>
With her came 4 monstrous golems, foul beings of magic with arms as thick as my sleek chest. Their claws tore the stones of the ground and ripped columns from their moorings as they strove to smother the spark of life that lived in me. I flung myself against the wall, and lay still on the ground. The mindless beings were unsure how they had bested me so easily and stood there for a moment. That was all the time we needed. My companion Mezzmorizer cast a mighty enchantment, and the 4 golems froze, drool slipping down the side of their chins, caught in dreams of their previous life, and their creator, unable to return to the reality in which they lay.<br>
<br>
Drusella however was not so easily fooled. She screamed out &quot;Useless druid-spawned-gnomeloving-creatures&quot; and rushed for kritical, rending his armour and tearing chunks from his flesh. Restoria was healing his wounds and keeping her at bay as best as she could, but Drusella was really really pisssed. I stood up and attacked with Lolodory from behind, ripping bones from her scrawny (yet not altogether un-attractive) carcass. Yet we were fighting a losing battle, Mezzmorizer was keeping her magically held in place, but she was too powerful, and the sources that sustained their magic were weakening. Then from behind me, an intense blast drove the foul witch back. Then another blast, this time greater than before, reeking of sufurous flame burst upon her, charring her bones into oblivion. A shout rang up upon the companions, the woman defeated. I rummaged through her belongings quickly and found the item which i desired. The urn which carried her memories of me, and mine of her, forced from our bodies and imprisoned in the urn by the evil Venril, which had tormented my dreams for years. I grabbed it and hugged it close to my chest as i beat a hasty retreat to my companions. Witherweaver nodded so slightly behind me and as i turned around my face froze with horror. The 4 monstrosities dreamlike expressions had vanished, and they were now severely angry with us. &quot;oh sh!t&quot; i exclaimed as i ran back to the group yelling &quot; ggogogogogogo&quot; Witherweaver began casting the magical portal that would take us out when i noticed Lolodory, digging through the gems that littered the floor. She would not notice the portal in time, and would be stuck to fend for herself. I grabbed her around the waist and flung her over my shoulder as i nimbly bounced into the ring of magics starting to coalesce around Witherweaver. As i set Lolodory down she kicked me hard, in the shins. Looking across the room while curled on the floor i noticed that in my haste to recover my friend, i had dropped the one item that would free me from my nightmares, the one testament of my true love for Drusella, and the one item that would allow me to spend eternity with her when i finally departed. As the magics closed around me, i sprang out, an agonising call of failure and loss tearing from my lips, reaching out my hands for this, my history, my only hope at love, and my memories of my beloved. the tips of my fingers brushed one last time against the cool blue porcelain, a faint glimpe of her in my arms, and then the 6 companions, me included, vanished into thin air. Appearing moments later hundreds of miles away. I concluded our mission, and silently walked away. I spent 100 days in meditation contemplating that which had forced my desires away from the center of my attention, that had cost me everlasting happiness, that which i would never rank high on my priorities again: Friendship.<br>
